data.name: CopyTableRowEvent
desc: specifies an event happening while copying table data between databases.
Whenever this event is fired to an XCopyTableListener, com::sun::star::lang::EventObject::Source contains the wizard instance which actually does the copying.

items.name: Error
lines: denotes the error which happened while copying the data.
Usually, this contains an instance of com::sun::star::sdbc::SQLException.

items.name: SourceData
lines: contains the result set which is being copied by the wizard currently.
